  "style": "",
  "texts": [
    "For symmetric noise, we flip the labels in each class randomly to incorrect labels of other classes.",
    "For asymmetric noise, we flip the labels within a specific set of classes.",
    "For CIFAR-10, flipping TRUCK → AUTOMOBILE, BIRD → AIRPLANE, DEER → HORSE, CAT ↔ DOG.",
    "For CIFAR-100, the 100 classes are grouped into 20 super-classes with each has 5 sub-classes, and each class are flipped within the same super-class into the next in a circular fashion.",
    "We vary the noise rate η ∈ {0.2, 0.4, 0.6, 0.8} for symmetric noise and η ∈ {0.2, 0.4} for asymmetric noise."
  ],
